change and the indigenous communities that

00:10:00.880 --> 00:10:03.730
actually depend on these resources to stay
alive.

00:10:03.730 --> 00:10:07.800
And then finally the Patagonia Coast where
Claudio and a number of people who work for

00:10:07.800 --> 00:10:13.280
him and partner with him are protecting the
largest continental population of Southern

00:10:13.280 --> 00:10:18.730
elephant seals, penguins, albatross, in a
way, in protecting and restoring that abundance

00:10:18.730 --> 00:10:21.350
in a way that is unprecedented around the
planet.

00:10:21.350 --> 00:10:27.480
So there is incredible hope and incredible
demonstrated success of places where weíre

00:10:27.480 --> 00:10:32.690
improving the health of the oceans and saving
a number of species and ecosystems.

00:10:32.690 --> 00:10:35.340
Iím just gonna close with a few slides.

00:10:35.340 --> 00:10:39.480
Some narrow slices of anecdotes that I think
are quite interesting.

00:10:39.480 --> 00:10:44.450
These are several of our Indonesian staff
working together with some fisherman in Indonesia

00:10:44.450 --> 00:10:50.530
that previously had used cyanide to fish for
the live reef fish trade; to take reef fish

00:10:50.530 --> 00:10:54.040
